59300010-773b-467a-9a29-73347093dbb2.do_description: To make the output, you have to...alternatively boxes going down fill in colors
59300010-773b-467a-9a29-73347093dbb2.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same
59300010-773b-467a-9a29-73347093dbb2.see_description: In the input, you should see...two colors of boxes

6283bd3d-71fe-4ae7-a27c-52761208cc37.do_description: To make the output, you have to... put a space in between each color going down. Then do the same on both sides of that line except skip the first box and leave it black. Do the same for the other if there is another color box.
6283bd3d-71fe-4ae7-a27c-52761208cc37.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same
6283bd3d-71fe-4ae7-a27c-52761208cc37.see_description: In the input, you should see... a color box or two in the grid

a164bc79-540c-42db-b183-234eb15dac40.do_description: To make the output, you have to...take each color and think of it as a 3 column checkerboard. For each color included, you need to go down and put that color in the opposite spot of the last row. For example, if the color is in the center on the first row, the second row would have color in column one and three. The next row would go back to color in column 2, and so on.
a164bc79-540c-42db-b183-234eb15dac40.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input grid.
a164bc79-540c-42db-b183-234eb15dac40.see_description: In the input, you should see...either one or two colored squares at the top of the grid. The rest should be all black.

c1a19e56-71df-4467-82a5-3673ab585571.do_description: To make the output, you have to...take it as 3 column for each square and fill as a chess board pattern
c1a19e56-71df-4467-82a5-3673ab585571.grid_description: The output grid size...is as same as the input grid
c1a19e56-71df-4467-82a5-3673ab585571.see_description: In the input, you should see...2 color squares the top of the grid and the rest are blank

d8d2b488-a4b6-4cbf-bf1d-8fcbf761eea6.do_description: To make the output, you have to...make it look like a checkerboard: use the top square provided, the next row will be staggered color, blank, color; the next row will be one square, and so on and so forth to the end. The second colored square represents a new checkerboard design following the same rules. Use the same colors as the starting colored square provided.
d8d2b488-a4b6-4cbf-bf1d-8fcbf761eea6.grid_description: The output grid size...should be similar.
d8d2b488-a4b6-4cbf-bf1d-8fcbf761eea6.see_description: In the input, you should see...either one or two colored squares at the top of the grid.
